From 5a9b01e8b866b6f670fe7f20addfce7917e79c52 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 07:04:53 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] test/common: run unittest_throttle serially

The BackoffThrottle tests assert the time-averaged occupancy the
throttle settles at, e.g. (35, 45) for undersaturated with
low_threshhold 0.4 of max 100. The equilibrium near the threshold only
forms when the getter threads can outrun the putters' drain rate, which
has implicitly assumed an unloaded machine since the tests were
introduced in 9f4cba31d7f ("Throttle: add BackoffThrottle unit tests").
On a saturated ctest run the getters get preempted, the arrival rate
drops below the drain rate even with no backoff delay injected, and the
occupancy sags below the asserted band (observed 26.6 < 35 repeatedly
under a full -j63 make check), failing the test although the throttle
behaves correctly.

Mark the test RUN_SERIAL so ctest runs it alone, restoring the
premise. It takes ~20s, a negligible serial window for the suite.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/test/common/CMakeLists.txt | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/test/common/CMakeLists.txt b/src/test/common/CMakeLists.txt
index 0765f0c2efd..934ae802834 100644
--- a/src/test/common/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/test/common/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -166,7 +166,8 @@ add_executable(unittest_throttle
   $<TARGET_OBJECTS:unit-main>
   )
 add_ceph_unittest(unittest_throttle PARALLEL)
-target_link_libraries(unittest_throttle global) 
+set_property(TEST unittest_throttle PROPERTY RUN_SERIAL TRUE)
+target_link_libraries(unittest_throttle global)
 
 # unittest_lru
 add_executable(unittest_lru
